meanings.definition: Past tense of fellate: to perform fellatio on someone.
meanings.sent1: She fellated her partner with care.
meanings.sent2: He fellated his lover as an act of intimacy.
meanings.sent3: The comedian joked about someone being fellated by accident.
meanings.sent4: The idea of being fellated by the wind sounded strangely poetic.
meanings.sent5: The image of being fellated by a vacuum cleaner is hard to forget.
